O2Jam Map Set Object¶

class reamber.o2jam.O2JMapSetObj.O2JMapSetObj(songId: int = 0, signature: str = '', encodeVersion: float = 0.0, genre: int = 0, bpm: float = 0.0, level: List[int] = <factory>, eventCount: List[int] = <factory>, noteCount: List[int] = <factory>, measureCount: List[int] = <factory>, packageCount: List[int] = <factory>, oldEncodeVersion: int = 0, oldSongId: int = 0, oldGenre: bytes = b'', bmpSize: int = 0, oldFileVersion: int = 0, title: str = '', artist: str = '', creator: str = '', ojmFile: str = '', coverSize: int = 0, duration: List[int] = <factory>, noteOffset: List[int] = <factory>, coverOffset: int = 0, maps: List[reamber.o2jam.O2JMapObj.O2JMapObj] = <factory>)¶

Bases: reamber.o2jam.O2JMapSetObjMeta.O2JMapSetObjMeta

This holds all data of OJN with a few exceptions

Exceptions:

  • Cover Data

  • Key Sounds Data + Placement

This also doesn’t support OJM (IO) and OJN (O).

OJM is not supported due to its complexity. OJN writing isn’t supported due to lack of support.

We won’t support OJM for now, we’ll just deal with OJN since it’s much easier.
